Development Summary Report: competency_widget Refactoring
This report provides a concise breakdown of the architectural, functional, and performance optimizations applied to the Moodle Competency Widget Block during today's development session. The plugin has been successfully refactored from a basic monolithic script into a modern, production-grade Moodle component.

1. Architectural Evolution & Refactoring
Separation of Concerns (MVC Pattern): Completely decoupled the backend PHP business logic from the presentation layer. Hardcoded HTML and CSS strings were entirely removed from block_competency_widget.php.

Mustache Templating Engine: Introduced templates/widget_content.mustache to handle the DOM layout natively via Moodle's core rendering engine.

External Stylesheet Optimization: Shifted all layout definitions into a standalone styles.css file in the plugin root. This enables browser-side caching and automated minification by Moodle's theme manager.

2. Functional & Context-Aware Enhancements
Multi-Pipeline Data Aggregation: Upgraded the data layer to concurrently fetch both site-wide Learning Plans and active Course Enrollments.

Dynamic Context Filtering: Programmed the block to recognize its environment layout:

Dashboard Mode: Aggregates and displays all site-wide tracking items.

Course Mode: Automatically detects the active course page and cleanses the view to isolate only the competencies mapped to that specific classroom context.

Deep Deep-Linking: Replaced static text labels with dynamic, context-aware Moodle hyperlinks (moodle_url), routing users directly to their detailed competency profiles or course tracking summaries upon clicking.

3. UI, Layout, & Sidebar Resilience
Dual-Badge Dashboard Layout: Expanded the item tracking cards to render a cleaner dual-marker interface:

Status Badge: Displays an active state marker using language-string mappings (Proficient or In Progress).

Context Badge: Displays where the skill requirement originates (Learning Plan or the specific Course Shortname).

Sidebar Fluid Resiliency: Resolved a layout defect where long course titles or competency descriptions caused container breakouts and horizontal scrollbars in narrow sidebars.

Ellipsis & Native Tooltips: Implemented defensive CSS Flexbox rules (min-width: 0, flex-shrink: 0) and relative capping definitions (max-width: 75px). Extra-long text strings now truncate gracefully with a trailing ellipsis (...) while retaining full-text readouts natively on mouse-hover via the HTML title attribute.

4. Performance Engineering & Technical Bug Fixes
Ad-Hoc Request Caching Engine: Resolved a critical Moodle system deadlock exception (The requested cache definition does not exist) by moving away from database-dependent cache configurations. Implemented an in-memory ad-hoc cache using cache::make_from_params() under MODE_REQUEST, reducing database strain across a single page lifecycle without requiring forced version-upgrade hooks.

Defensive Type-Cast Mapping: Fixed a silent execution failure where the block rendered empty despite data existing. Patched the core loop with defensive is_object() mapping checks to correctly catch Moodle API data types (stdClass variations vs. associative arrays).

Internationalization Engine Sync: Replaced remaining hardcoded English text strings with Moodle's global localization method (get_string()), fully aligning the controller logic with the placeholder design configuration inside your lang/en/ translation strings file.

5. Pure CSS SVG Chart Stabilization
Elimination of JS Race Conditions: Discovered that asynchronous page loading loops on Moodle dashboards caused the progress ring to experience timing dropouts (remaining gray).

Zero-Dependency Approach: Safely removed the legacy AMD JavaScript module layer (amd/src/init.js) entirely. The exact $strokeoffset metric is now injected directly into the SVG container properties from the server side on render.

Hardware-Accelerated Animation: Integrated a lightweight CSS @keyframes animation loop that smoothly transitions the progress ring from 0% up to the exact completion metric instantly upon page mounting.